import { Component, OnInit } from "@angular/core"; @Component({ selector: "app-about", templateUrl: "./about.component.html", styleUrls: ["./about.component.scss"], }) export class AboutComponent implements OnInit { constructor() {} ngOnInit(): void {} }

Hi, my name is Reni , and I am absolut in love with coding.

I have always been fascinated by the intersection of art and technology, and I have never been afraid to dive in and try it out, whether it's Paint, Photoshop, or CSS.

In 2022, after completing my degree in economics, I finally immersed myself in coding and web development.

I have a strong passion for design work, and I enjoy inventing and implementing new things and animations. Additionally, since completing the SGD development training, I have been increasingly involved in creating server-side applications, which I also really enjoy.

Currently, I am working every day to become a full-stack developer.

I know the journey ahead is long, but I am enjoying every step of it. I am eager to collaborate with like-minded individuals who share the same enthusiasm.
